00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
The village of Ravenswood was never the same after the night the stranger arrived.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:09,440
He was tall and imposing, with eyes that seemed to see right through you.

3
00:00:09,440 --> 00:00:14,680
He wore a long black coat, covered in blood stains, and carried a large, leather-bound

4
00:00:14,680 --> 00:00:16,440
book under his arm.

5
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:21,440
No one knew where he came from, but he appeared out of nowhere, as if summoned by some dark

6
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:22,440
force.

7
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:27,440
He took up residence in the abandoned manor on the hill, surrounded by a forest that seemed

8
00:00:27,440 --> 00:00:31,800
to grow more twisted and gnarled with each passing day.

9
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:37,200
Rumors spread like wildfire through the village, each one more outlandish than the last.

10
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:41,120
Some said he was a vampire, praying on the innocent at night.

11
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:45,160
Others claimed he was a demon, summoned from the depths of hell to bring about the end

12
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:46,160
of days.

13
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:47,960
But I knew the truth.

14
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:52,880
I had seen him, standing in the shadows of my own garden, his eyes fixed on me with an

15
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:56,000
